subSubSection.paragraph:
Prothorax
: Prosternum anteromedially (before procoxae) somewhat vaulted and coarsely sculptured; laterally (before propleuron) smooth and shiny, without punctures. Hypomeron in anterior half laterally narrowly flattened, becoming broader anteriad; flat region with some coarse lengthy punctures and long setae (
Fig. 3b
); rest of hypomeron and propleuron smooth and shiny. Prosternal column ascending posteriad (as viewed if beetle turned upside down), between procoxae with a few transverse ridges. Prosternal process weakly inclined, broadly lanceolate, apex broadly rounded (
Fig. 2b
); with distinct broad longitudinal parallel-sided furrow; furrow formed by a few very coarse and closely arranged punctures, sides of furrow strongly rimmed; right and left of furrow process strongly descending. Apex of process reaching between mesocoxae and here touching anteromedial process of metaventrite.
